                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Relevant Cases</strong> : This resource includes summaries of relevant court decisions and case law that interpret and apply the statutory provisions. By highlighting judicial precedents, the USCA helps users 
                                understand how the law has been interpreted in practice.</li><br>
                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Cross-References </strong> : To facilitate research and analysis, the USCA includes cross-references to related statutory provisions, regulations, and legal treatises, allowing users to navigate complex legal topics 
                                and explore interconnected areas of law.</li><br>
                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Updates</strong> : Regularly updated to reflect changes in legislation, judicial decisions, and legal scholarship, the USCA ensures that users have access to the most
                                 current and authoritative information available.</li>                   
                            </ul>

                            <h4 class="mb-3">Benefits :</h4>
                            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Comprehensive Coverage</strong> : Covering a wide range of legal topics, the USCA provides comprehensive coverage of federal law, including statutes enacted by Congress and regulations 
                                issued by federal agencies.</li><br>
                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Practical Insights</strong> :  With its detailed annotations and commentary, the USCA offers practical insights into the application and interpretation of federal law, helping users navigate
                                 legal issues and develop informed legal strategies.</li><br>
                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Research Efficiency </strong> : By consolidating statutory text, case law, and commentary in a single resource, the USCA streamlines legal research and analysis, saving users time and effort in
                                 locating relevant legal sources and authorities.</li><br>
                                <li><i class="fa fa-angle-right text-primary me-2"></i><strong>Audience</strong> : The United States Code Annotated is indispensable for legal professionals, including attorneys, judges, law students, and researchers, seeking authoritative and reliable 
                                guidance on federal law matters.</li>                   
                            </ul>
                                   
